ğŸ“„ Report
1. Challenges

Audio Format Restrictions: Vosk requires mono PCM WAV at 8kHz or 16kHz; incorrect input caused errors.

Background Noise: Recognition accuracy dropped in noisy environments.

Command Parsing: Free speech is hard to parse into commands, so we restricted to keywords (â€œopenâ€, â€œcloseâ€, â€œtimeâ€).

2. Trade-offs

Offline vs. Online:

Offline (Vosk) â†’ Privacy, no internet required, but larger models and slower on weak CPUs.

Online (Google Speech API) â†’ More accurate, but needs internet.

Lightweight Model vs. Large Model:

Small model (vosk-model-small-en-in-0.4) is fast but less accurate.

Larger models are accurate but need more RAM/CPU.

3. Improvements

Add wake word detection (â€œHey Sonicâ€) before processing commands.

Extend inventory/order handling (e.g., â€œadd 2 coffees, 1 breadâ€).

Integrate with a GUI or Web Dashboard for better interaction.

Add multilingual support by switching Vosk models.

âœ… End-to-End functionality is tested with sample audio inputs (order.wav, live mic speech).
